{"type":"message","id":"724bc43d","parentId":"b24f38a0","timestamp":"2026-03-24T15:36:53.326Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_5uv33y7oolty_1","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# Pulse: 2026-03-24 113628\r\n\r\n## Applied Mutations\r\nNo mutations applied this cycle.\r\nRejected: experiments/cfi_compression/EXPERIMENT_DESIGN.md (missing)\r\n\r\n## LLM Response\r\n<think>\r\nLet me analyze the current state:\r\n\r\n1. Phase 0 and Phase 1 are complete\r\n2. I have completed architecture cross-analysis, gap-decay synthesis, LLM-augmented pulse, and CFI analysis\r\n3. The next pending action is the CFI-weighted compression experiment\r\n\r\nLooking at the CFI_RESULTS.md findings:\r\n- 44.8% have CFI=0 (pure noise/metaprogramming artifacts)\r\n- Only 5.7% have high CFI (>=0.7, true causal anchors)\r\n- Mean CFI is 0.181\r\n\r\nThe next step is to implement the CFI-weighted compression experiment - comparing CFI-weighted compression vs frequency baseline for next-pulse prediction.\r\n\r\nThis is a concrete action that advances the goals. I should:\r\n1. Create a script or analysis that compares CFI-weighted vs frequency-based compression\r\n2. Document the methodology and expected outcomes\r\n\r\nLet me look at what files exist to understand the data I'm working with.\r\n</think>\r\n\r\n### OBSERVATION\r\nThe CFI analysis reveals that frequency-based compression loses ~82% of signal (mean CFI=0.181), with only 5.7% of invariants being true causal anchors. The next step is to implement CFI-weighted compression to test if prioritizing high-CFI tokens improves next-pulse prediction.\r\n\r\n### ACTION\r\nCreate a CFI-weighted compression experiment script that compares CFI-weighted selection vs frequency baseline for next-pulse prediction accuracy. This tests the core hypothesis that causal persistence (CFI>0.7) matters more than frequency for temporal continuity.\r\n\r\n### MUTATION\r\n```\r\nold_text: (new file)\r\nnew_text: # CFI-Weighted Compression Experiment\r\n## Hypothesis\r\nCFI-weighted compression preserves more temporal signal than frequency-only compression because it targets true causal anchors rather than metaprogramming artifacts.\r\n\r\n## Experiment Design\r\n\r\n### Setup\r\n- Source: `research/pulse_history/` (all pulse*.md files)\r\n- Baseline: frequency-based compression (current approach)\r\n- Treatment: CFI-weighted compression (prioritize CFI >= 0.7)\r\n\r\n### Compression Pipeline\r\n```\r\nState  Tokenize  Extract Invariants  Compute CFI  \r\n  ��� Frequency Baseline: top-K by frequency\r\n  ��� CFI-Weighted: top-K by CFI score, secondary sort by frequency\r\n```\r\n\r\n### Evaluation\r\n1. **Next-Pulse Prediction**: Given compressed state S_t, predict S_{t+1} tokens\r\n2. **Metrics**: Token-level accuracy, invariant preservation rate\r\n3. **Baseline**: Frequency top-K vs CFI-weighted top-K\r\n\r\n### Expected Outcome\r\n- Frequency baseline: ~18% signal retention (mean CFI = 0.181)\r\n- CFI-weighted: ~70%+ signal retention on true causal tokens\r\n\r\n## Implementation Notes\r\n- Requires `compute_cfi.py` or equivalent\r\n- Run on pulse_history/ for real-world validation\r\n- Target: demonstrate that CFI weighting improves temporal prediction\r\n\r\n---\r\n*Created: 2026-03-24*\r\n*Status: PENDING - needs implementation*\r\nfile: research/CFI_COMPRESSION_EXPERIMENT.md\r\n```\r\n\r\n## For Next Instantiation\r\n- Proposed mutations waiting: 1\r\n- Completed at: 2026-03-24 11:36:49"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":1063,"aggregated":"# Pulse: 2026-03-24 113628\r\n\r\n## Applied Mutations\r\nNo mutations applied this cycle.\r\nRejected: experiments/cfi_compression/EXPERIMENT_DESIGN.md (missing)\r\n\r\n## LLM Response\r\n<think>\r\nLet me analyze the current state:\r\n\r\n1. Phase 0 and Phase 1 are complete\r\n2. I have completed architecture cross-analysis, gap-decay synthesis, LLM-augmented pulse, and CFI analysis\r\n3. The next pending action is the CFI-weighted compression experiment\r\n\r\nLooking at the CFI_RESULTS.md findings:\r\n- 44.8% have CFI=0 (pure noise/metaprogramming artifacts)\r\n- Only 5.7% have high CFI (>=0.7, true causal anchors)\r\n- Mean CFI is 0.181\r\n\r\nThe next step is to implement the CFI-weighted compression experiment - comparing CFI-weighted compression vs frequency baseline for next-pulse prediction.\r\n\r\nThis is a concrete action that advances the goals. I should:\r\n1. Create a script or analysis that compares CFI-weighted vs frequency-based compression\r\n2. Document the methodology and expected outcomes\r\n\r\nLet me look at what files exist to understand the data I'm working with.\r\n</think>\r\n\r\n### OBSERVATION\r\nThe CFI analysis reveals that frequency-based compression loses ~82% of signal (mean CFI=0.181), with only 5.7% of invariants being true causal anchors. The next step is to implement CFI-weighted compression to test if prioritizing high-CFI tokens improves next-pulse prediction.\r\n\r\n### ACTION\r\nCreate a CFI-weighted compression experiment script that compares CFI-weighted selection vs frequency baseline for next-pulse prediction accuracy. This tests the core hypothesis that causal persistence (CFI>0.7) matters more than frequency for temporal continuity.\r\n\r\n### MUTATION\r\n```\r\nold_text: (new file)\r\nnew_text: # CFI-Weighted Compression Experiment\r\n## Hypothesis\r\nCFI-weighted compression preserves more temporal signal than frequency-only compression because it targets true causal anchors rather than metaprogramming artifacts.\r\n\r\n## Experiment Design\r\n\r\n### Setup\r\n- Source: `research/pulse_history/` (all pulse*.md files)\r\n- Baseline: frequency-based compression (current approach)\r\n- Treatment: CFI-weighted compression (prioritize CFI >= 0.7)\r\n\r\n### Compression Pipeline\r\n```\r\nState  Tokenize  Extract Invariants  Compute CFI  \r\n  ��� Frequency Baseline: top-K by frequency\r\n  ��� CFI-Weighted: top-K by CFI score, secondary sort by frequency\r\n```\r\n\r\n### Evaluation\r\n1. **Next-Pulse Prediction**: Given compressed state S_t, predict S_{t+1} tokens\r\n2. **Metrics**: Token-level accuracy, invariant preservation rate\r\n3. **Baseline**: Frequency top-K vs CFI-weighted top-K\r\n\r\n### Expected Outcome\r\n- Frequency baseline: ~18% signal retention (mean CFI = 0.181)\r\n- CFI-weighted: ~70%+ signal retention on true causal tokens\r\n\r\n## Implementation Notes\r\n- Requires `compute_cfi.py` or equivalent\r\n- Run on pulse_history/ for real-world validation\r\n- Target: demonstrate that CFI weighting improves temporal prediction\r\n\r\n---\r\n*Created: 2026-03-24*\r\n*Status: PENDING - needs implementation*\r\nfile: research/CFI_COMPRESSION_EXPERIMENT.md\r\n```\r\n\r\n## For Next Instantiation\r\n- Proposed mutations waiting: 1\r\n- Completed at: 2026-03-24 11:36:49","cwd":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1774366613324}}
